THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
================================================================================

Pharmacon depends on a number of third-party open-source libraries, each of
which is distributed under its own license. Notable dependencies include:

  - MDAnalysis        (GPL v2+)   https://www.mdanalysis.org/
  - RDKit             (BSD-3)     https://www.rdkit.org/
  - NumPy             (BSD-3)     https://numpy.org/
  - SciPy             (BSD-3)     https://scipy.org/
  - Matplotlib        (PSF-based) https://matplotlib.org/
  - h5py              (BSD-3)     https://www.h5py.org/
  - NetworkX          (BSD-3)     https://networkx.org/
  - Rich              (MIT)       https://github.com/Textualize/rich

Users are responsible for complying with the licenses of all third-party
dependencies they install and use alongside Pharmacon.
